  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \"gross amount\"?",
  "response": "\"Gross amount\" refers to the total or complete amount of something before any deductions, such as taxes, expenses, discounts, or other reductions are applied. In financial terms, it represents the full or original value of an income, payment, or quantity. For example:\n\n1. In salary: Gross income is the total earnings before taxes and other deductions.\n2. In sales: Gross sales are the total revenue before subtracting returns, discounts, or allowances.\n3. In accounting: Gross amount is the full value of a financial item before any adjustments are made.\n\nThe opposite of gross amount is \"net amount,\" which is the value after deductions have been subtracted.",
